# General Project Rules

## Stack
Node.js + Express 5 + EJS + TypeScript + Mongoose. Entry: `app.ts`, DB bootstrap: `database.ts`.

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files; keep strict mode compatible with `tsconfig.json`.
- Follow existing controller pattern: named exports, `(req, res) => void` or returning `Promise`.
- Use Mongoose model instance methods for cart/order mutations (see `user.model.ts`).

## File Conventions
- Controllers → `controllers/*.controller.ts`
- Models → `models/*.model.ts`
- Routes → `routes/*.routes.ts`
- Views → `views/**/*.ejs` (Bootstrap-compatible markup)

## Do Not
- Do not reorder middleware in `app.ts` (tests depend on ordering).
- Do not remove or rename `req.user` — it is augmented globally in `global.d.ts`.

